│ pointers `%a` and `%b` have different provenance but the same address. My attempts to fix this have been too aggressive, disabling valid optimizations and causing regressions.          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The key insight is that the problematic optimization, `simplifySelectWithEquivalence`, is only valid if the pointer equality implies that the pointers are interchangeable. This is true │
│ if they are derived from the same underlying object, but false otherwise. My previous attempts to use `getUnderlyingObject` were on the right track but were implemented incorrectly,    │
│ leading to build failures or regressions.                                                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will take a more direct and robust approach. I will modify the `simplifySelectWithEquivalence` function itself. This function is where the incorrect substitution happens. I will add  │
│ a check at the beginning of this function to prevent it from running on pointer types altogether. This is a broader fix, but it is safer and less likely to have subtle side effects     │
│ than trying to patch the call sites. While this might miss some valid pointer-related optimizations, it will definitively fix the miscompilation and avoid the regressions I've been     │
│ seeing. This is a conservative but correct approach given the complexity of the issue.                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
